title: Paraclete drops second game in The Classic
text:
The Paraclete boys basketball team lost its second straight game in The Classic at Damien with a 55-48 loss to Aquinas on Wednesday at St. Lucy’s High School.
Mister Burnside led the Spirits (12-3) with 18 points and Devon Marshall scored 12 points.

The Paraclete boys basketball team lost its second straight game in The Classic at Damien with a 55-48 loss to Aquinas on Wednesday at St. Lucy’s High School.
Mister Burnside led the Spirits (12-3) with 18 points and Devon Marshall scored 12 points.
Paraclete’s DJ Phillips put in eight points, Moses Wright scored seven and Brett Novak added three points.
The Spirits play Palisades in the tournament’s Silver Bracket at 3 p.m. on Friday at Life Pacific University.

Girls Soccer
Quartz Hill 3, Ayala 0
The Quartz Hill girls soccer team defeated Ayala 3-0 on Wednesday in the Winter Classic.
It was the second time in two weeks that the Royals have defeated Ayala, winning 5-2 on Dec. 16 in a different tournament.
Quartz Hill is now 15-0 on the season.
The Royals play Granite Hills today in the Winter Classic.
Boys Soccer
Hart 1, Quartz Hill 0
Pacifica 2, Quartz Hill 0
The Quartz Hill boys soccer team lost two games in the Hart Soccer Showcase on Wednesday. The Royals fell 1-0 to Hart and 2-0 to Pacifica.
Quartz Hill goalkeeper Adrien Vizacarra saved one shot against Hart and had two saves against Pacifica. Kaleb Stokes had six shots against Hart.
